{"parse":{"title":"Tom Cohen","pageid":40408419,"revid":858246420,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Tom Cohen</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span class=\"nickname\">Tom Dana Cohen</span><br /><span style=\"display:none\"> (<span class=\"bday\">1953-08-13</span>) </span>August 13, 1953<span class=\"noprint ForceAgeToShow\"> (age&#160;65)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma&#160;mater</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Yale_University\" title=\"Yale University\">Yale University</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Occupation</th><td class=\"role\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Cultural_theorist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cultural theorist\">Cultural theorist</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Tom Dana Cohen</b> (born August 13, 1953),<sup id=\"cite_ref-Congress_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Congress-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is an American media and cultural theorist, currently a professor at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_at_Albany,_State_University_of_New_York\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University at Albany, State University of New York\">University at Albany, State University of New York</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  He has published numerous important books on <a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Hitchcock\" title=\"Alfred Hitchcock\">Alfred Hitchcock</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Cohen has also written on other aspects of <a href=\"/wiki/Film_studies\" title=\"Film studies\">film studies</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Comparative_literature\" title=\"Comparative literature\">comparative literature</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Theory\" title=\"Theory\">theory</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Cultural_studies\" title=\"Cultural studies\">cultural studies</a> and on <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_de_Man\" title=\"Paul de Man\">Paul de Man</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Cohen has also published broadly on American authors and ideology, including <a href=\"/wiki/Edgar_Allan_Poe\" title=\"Edgar Allan Poe\">Edgar Allan Poe</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Walt_Whitman\" title=\"Walt Whitman\">Walt Whitman</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Mikhail_Bakhtin\" title=\"Mikhail Bakhtin\">Mikhail Bakhtin</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/William_Faulkner\" title=\"William Faulkner\">William Faulkner</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Pragmatism\" title=\"Pragmatism\">pragmatism</a>, as well as on <a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Hitchcock\" title=\"Alfred Hitchcock\">Alfred Hitchcock</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Greek_philosophy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Greek philosophy\">Greek philosophy</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Continental_philosophy\" title=\"Continental philosophy\">continental philosophy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He is the editor (with <a href=\"/wiki/Claire_Colebrook\" title=\"Claire Colebrook\">Claire Colebrook</a>) of the Critical Climate Change Book Series at <a href=\"/wiki/Open_Humanities_Press\" title=\"Open Humanities Press\">Open Humanities Press</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and has lectured and taught  internationally, including in China and <a href=\"/wiki/Fulbright\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fulbright\">Fulbright</a> sponsored work in Thailand. He has been awarded a Distinguished Visiting Professorship by Shanghai Municipality in Shanghai.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Biography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Biography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected bibliography</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Books\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tom_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Cohen's education consists of a M.A. from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Chicago\" title=\"University of Chicago\">University of Chicago</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Comparative_Literature\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Comparative Literature\">Comparative Literature</a> and a Ph.D. from <a href=\"/wiki/Yale_University\" title=\"Yale University\">Yale University</a> in Comparative Literature. Thus Cohen\u2019s work began in <a href=\"/wiki/Literary_theory\" title=\"Literary theory\">literary theory</a> and cultural politics but he has then explored as a <a href=\"/wiki/Philosopher\" title=\"Philosopher\">philosopher</a> areas of <a href=\"/wiki/Critical_theory\" title=\"Critical theory\">critical theory</a>, cinema studies, <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_media\" title=\"Digital media\">digital media</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Climate_change\" title=\"Climate change\">climate change</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_bibliography\">Selected bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tom_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tom_Cohen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, Tom (1994). <i>Anti-mimesis from Plato to Hitchcock</i>. Cambridge New York, NY, USA: Cambridge University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780521465847\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780521465847\">9780521465847</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anti-mimesis+from+Plato+to+Hitchcock&amp;rft.place=Cambridge+New+York%2C+NY%2C+USA&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=9780521465847&amp;rft.aulast=Cohen&amp;rft.aufirst=Tom&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATom+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<dl><dd><dl><dd>Reviewed in: <cite id=\"CITEREFSzalay1995\" class=\"citation journal\">Szalay, Michael (1995). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dx.doi.org/10.1111/edth.12034\">\"Book review: Anti-mimesis from Plato to Hitchcock\"</a>. <i>MLN</i>. Project MUSE, The Johns Hopkins University Press. <b>110</b> (4): 983\u2013985. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1111/edth.12034\">10.1111/edth.12034</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=MLN&amp;rft.atitle=Book+review%3A+Anti-mimesis+from+Plato+to+Hitchcock&amp;rft.volume=110&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=983-985&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fedth.12034&amp;rft.aulast=Szalay&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdx.doi.org%2F10.1111%2Fedth.12034&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATom+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, Tom (1998). <i>Ideology and inscription: \"cultural studies\" after Benjamin, de Man, and Bakhtin</i>. Cambridge, UK New York: Cambridge University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780521599672\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780521599672\">9780521599672</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ideology+and+inscription%3A+%22cultural+studies%22+after+Benjamin%2C+de+Man%2C+and+Bakhtin&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+UK+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.isbn=9780521599672&amp;rft.aulast=Cohen&amp;rft.aufirst=Tom&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATom+Cohen\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Cohen, Tom (2001). <i>Jacques Derrida and the humanities a critical reader</i>. Cambridge, U.K. New York: Cambridge University Press. <a href=\"